  "texts": [
    "To then generate landslide hazard estimates, as per the definition proposed by Guzzetti et al. (1999), we added a step where the pseudo-probability of landslide occurrence is multiplied by the landslide area density.",
    "Notably, the developed model is spatio-temporal because it is built to explain the variability of the landslide hazard in space and time.",
    "However, the convolution layers used in this modeling approach are of a 2D nature.",
    "Therefore, the spatial structure in the data is handled via the 2D CNN, whereas the connection between subsequent spatial layers is not explicitly built in.",
    "The landslide hazard definition includes the concept of return periods to treat the temporal component, where for a given triggering situation of a given return period, the landslide hazard is estimated."
  ],
